race.comment: LONG SERVICE LEAF (5) won impressively on debut before sitting close to the speed and finishing 1L away last time out when a $1.55 favourite. Into a CL3 now where he drops in weight. Back to 1000m might do the trick and with a touch of luck from the barrier, he can return to winning ways. MAGICASH (4) is unbeaten first-up and looks on song judging by her recent trial under Pike at Lark Hill. She comes into this off a short break after finishing well back in this grade at Bunbury 76 days ago. She's better than she showed that day and if she can run up to what she did first-up last campaign, she'll be hard to beat. CALL OF DUTY (3) just missed last start at Bunbury when beaten 0.9L. The form out of that race has been sound and he can put his best foot forward from an inside barrier. COONDLE (1) should get a good run in transit and can make his presence felt. SUNLIT FRESCO (2) drops right back in grade today and can turn her form around.
